      <description>&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I am a first-year Ph.D. student in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.meiji.ac.jp/cip/english/graduate/ams/index.html&#34;&gt;Graduate School of Advanced Mathematical Sciences&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.meiji.ac.jp/cip/english/&#34;&gt;Meiji University&lt;/a&gt;. I also work as a &lt;a href=&#34;https://gyoseki1.mind.meiji.ac.jp/mjuhp/KgApp?resId=S003902&amp;amp;Language=2&#34;&gt;Research Associate&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.meiji.ac.jp/cip/english/undergraduate/ims/index.html&#34;&gt;School of Interdisciplinary Mathematical Sciences&lt;/a&gt;.&#xA;My research revolves around complex systems, exploring topics ranging from social dynamics to mathematical biology. I use tools from statistical physics, mathematics, and computation to uncover the fundamental principles underlying a diverse array of phenomena.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;&#xA;&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;</description>
